implementation_notes:
FEATURE ID: CC-0114 (GitHub issue #412). Scope: move the K-ORC bootstrap clouds.yaml seed from deploy-infra shell into reconcileKORC, add a per-CR operator-owned ExternalSecret, and remove the now-dead shell seed + KORC_KEYSTONE_AUTH_URL knob + the openstack-namespace static ExternalSecret. NO new RBAC/CRD/condition (boundary 8, 11).

=== KEY ARCHITECTURE DECISIONS ===
1) DECISION (placement) — the issue says 'after ensureAdminPasswordCloud and ensureAppCredentialSecret AND before ensureKORCAdminImports', but the real call order in reconcile_korc.go is ensureAdminPasswordCloud(345) -> ensureKORCAdminImports(383) -> ensureAppCredentialSecret(410) -> re-mint/CreateOrUpdate AC switch(428). Those two constraints are inconsistent. CHOSEN: insert the three new steps immediately AFTER ensureAppCredentialSecret(410) and BEFORE the switch(428). Reasons: (a) the seed writes into the {cp.Name}-admin-app-credential Secret that ensureAppCredentialSecret creates/owns, so running after it updates one Secret rather than racing two CreateOrUpdate calls; (b) all three steps then run on every pass before the mint, so the OpenBao path is populated and ESO can materialize the ExternalSecret; (c) the 'before ensureKORCAdminImports' intent (let imports authenticate) is moot because K-ORC retries authentication asynchronously (stated in the issue), so the relative order vs the imports CR creation within one synchronous pass does not change convergence; (d) minimal change — three inserted calls, no reordering. Leave a `// DECISION: ... Reviewer: please verify` comment at the insertion point.
2) DECISION (helper vs inline) — there is NO EnsureExternalSecret helper in internal/common/secrets (only WaitForExternalSecret + EnsurePushSecret, both confirmed). The operator already uses inline controllerutil.CreateOrUpdate + SetControllerReference everywhere (Secrets, Domain/User/Service/Endpoint CRs). CHOSEN: add a private method ensureKORCCloudsYAMLExternalSecret on *ControlPlaneReconciler using inline CreateOrUpdate (mirror the Domain import / Catalog Service pattern). Do NOT add a generic helper to internal/common/secrets — single caller, YAGNI (simplicity-first).
3) ESO API VERSIONS — CRITICAL: PushSecret is esov1alpha1 (github.com/external-secrets/external-secrets/apis/externalsecrets/v1alpha1, already imported). ExternalSecret is esov1 (.../externalsecrets/v1) — reconcile_korc.go does NOT yet import esov1; add `esov1 "github.com/external-secrets/external-secrets/apis/externalsecrets/v1"`. korcTestScheme already registers BOTH (esov1 + esov1alpha1), so unit tests need no scheme change.
4) FIELD NAMES (verified against the pinned apis module v0.0.0-20260603083646-a38e5b08e076): esov1.ExternalSecretSpec{SecretStoreRef esov1.SecretStoreRef, Target esov1.ExternalSecretTarget, Data []esov1.ExternalSecretData, RefreshInterval *metav1.Duration}; SecretStoreRef{Name, Kind}; ExternalSecretTarget{Name, CreationPolicy esov1.ExternalSecretCreationPolicy}; the Owner enum constant is esov1.CreatePolicyOwner (literal "Owner") — NOTE the name is CreatePolicyOwner, not CreationPolicyOwner; ExternalSecretData{SecretKey string, RemoteRef esov1.ExternalSecretDataRemoteRef}; ExternalSecretDataRemoteRef{Key, Property}. Optionally set RefreshInterval to 1h (&metav1.Duration{Duration: time.Hour}; 'time' is already imported) to match the retired static manifest.

=== EXACT FUNCTION SKELETONS ===
func (r *ControlPlaneReconciler) seedBootstrapCloudsYAML(ctx, cp, password) error {
  cloudsYAML := []byte(buildPasswordCloudsYAML(cp, password))
  secret := &corev1.Secret{ObjectMeta:{Name: adminAppCredentialSecretName(cp), Namespace: childNamespace(cp)}}
  CreateOrUpdate(... func() error {
    if secret.Data == nil { secret.Data = map[string][]byte{} }
    if len(secret.Data[appCredCloudsYAMLKey]) == 0 { secret.Data[appCredCloudsYAMLKey] = cloudsYAML }
    return SetControllerReference(cp, secret, r.Scheme) })
}
func (r *ControlPlaneReconciler) ensureKORCCloudsYAMLExternalSecret(ctx, cp) error {
  name := cp.Spec.KORC.AdminCredential.CloudCredentialsRef.SecretName; if name=="" { name = korcCloudsYamlSecretName }
  es := &esov1.ExternalSecret{ObjectMeta:{Name: name, Namespace: childNamespace(cp)}}
  CreateOrUpdate(... func() error {
    es.Spec.SecretStoreRef = esov1.SecretStoreRef{Kind:"ClusterSecretStore", Name: openBaoClusterStoreName}
    es.Spec.Target = esov1.ExternalSecretTarget{Name: name, CreationPolicy: esov1.CreatePolicyOwner}
    es.Spec.Data = []esov1.ExternalSecretData{{SecretKey: appCredCloudsYAMLKey, RemoteRef: esov1.ExternalSecretDataRemoteRef{Key: adminAppCredentialRemoteKeyFor(cp), Property: appCredCloudsYAMLKey}}}
    return SetControllerReference(cp, es, r.Scheme) })
}
In reconcileKORC after line 410: call seedBootstrapCloudsYAML; then secrets.EnsurePushSecret(ctx, r.Client, r.Scheme, cp, adminAppCredentialPushSecret(cp)); then ensureKORCCloudsYAMLExternalSecret. Wrap each in the existing KORCReady=False/SetCondition+return pattern (distinct Reasons e.g. SeedCloudsYamlError, PushSecretError, ExternalSecretError).

=== ARCHITECTURE / DATA FLOW (>3 components) ===
Components: ControlPlaneReconciler.reconcileKORC -> {cp.Name}-admin-app-credential Secret (clouds.yaml key) -> PushSecret -> OpenBao (openstack/keystone/{ns}/{name}/admin/app-credential) -> ESO ClusterSecretStore -> operator-owned ExternalSecret (childNamespace) -> k-orc-clouds-yaml Secret -> K-ORC admin imports + reconcileAdminCredential gate.
Fresh-cluster data flow:
  reconcileKORC: readAdminPassword -> ensureAdminPasswordCloud -> ensureKORCAdminImports -> ensureAppCredentialSecret
     -> [NEW] seedBootstrapCloudsYAML (password clouds.yaml, write-if-empty)
     -> [NEW] EnsurePushSecret (mirror Secret.clouds.yaml -> OpenBao path)
     -> [NEW] ensureKORCCloudsYAMLExternalSecret (per-CR ES reading that path)
     -> CreateOrUpdate AC (K-ORC mints) -> KORCReady
  ESO materializes k-orc-clouds-yaml Secret (childNamespace) from the seeded path -> reconcileAdminCredential gate opens
  reconcileAdminCredential: assembles credential-based clouds.yaml -> Secret.clouds.yaml (overwrites the seed) -> EnsurePushSecret (no-op) -> AdminCredentialReady
Re-mint: regenerateAppCredentialSecretValue deletes clouds.yaml key -> next reconcileKORC re-seeds the password version -> bridges re-auth gap.

=== PITFALLS ===
- Use esov1 for ExternalSecret, esov1alpha1 for PushSecret — mixing them will not compile.
- CreatePolicyOwner spelling (not CreationPolicyOwner); the field set is Target.CreationPolicy.
- Keep the seed write-if-empty: a plain assignment would clobber the minted credential on every pass and re-push to OpenBao (churn + wrong auth after rotation).
- Do NOT touch the 'value' key in the seed (ensureAppCredentialSecret owns it; clobbering it would force a re-mint).
- reconcileAdminCredential is unchanged except the PushSecret call already there becomes a no-op; do not move the mint or the clouds.yaml-fill logic.
- The orc-system static ExternalSecret stays (cross-namespace owner refs are disallowed; it is off the AdminCredentialReady critical path) — only the openstack-namespace document is removed.
- No make manifests/generate (no *_types.go change); a regenerated-CRD diff in review signals an accidental type change.
- Patterns to follow: Kubernetes Operator Reconciliation (idempotent create-or-update, write-if-empty), External Secrets over direct Secret writes, GitOps (operator owns per-CR ES, orc-system stays declarative), field-ownership (one owner per object).
